  "bio_raw": "Andalib Rubayat  is currently working as a senior lecturer in the Media Studies and Journalism Department at the University of Liberal Arts, Bangladesh. Before joining ULAB, he worked as an adjunct lecturer at the Institute of Comparative Literature and Culture at Jahangirnagar University.\nHe completed his MA at the New York Film Academy (Los Angeles) and has over 10 years of experience working in media productions. His short film \"Deceased\" was screened at the renowned Warner Bros. Studio. Later, it was screened at 12 international film festivals. His COVID film \"Life Was Beautiful\" has been screened at 17 international film festivals and won 14 best film awards in different categories. A case video he worked on as director of photography, \"The Impossipuzzle Poster,\" became a finalist at the prestigious Cannes Lions International Festival of Creativity.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Film Studies, Film Adaptation, Auteurism and Authorship"
  ],
